<TITLE> PM assures youths of bright future </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 08 (bdnews24.com) -- Prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Tuesday urged the young generation to play a pioneering role in socio-economic development of the country. Sheikh Hasina said the government has initiated different steps to ensure a shining future for the youths of the country. The prime minister was addressing at the launch of a programme marking National Youth Day at Osmani Memorial auditorium on Tuesday. She said the country failed to achieve prosperity at an expected level even after 38 years of independence because democratic process was not allowed to run uninterrupted. Many countries which won independence after ours have made great stride while we are lagging behind, she said The prime minister blamed military autocracy for the situation. She said, "The nation which won independence through struggle can not lag behind. We want to prosper by utilizing the talent and creativity of our young generation." Referring to drug as a major problem, Sheikh Hasina said, "It is now a global phenomenon." "We want to build a country free from corruption, drug and terrorism," she said The prime minister handed over awards among 10 youths at the programme. The recipients of the award are Anwar Hossain from Dhaka Division, Ohid Ullah from Chittagong Division, ABM Lajem from Rajshahi Division, Mahmudul Hasan from Sylhet Division, youth organisers Zakir Hossain, Rahima Sultana, Nahid Sultana Tripti from female quota and Binoy Jyoti from tribal quota. The programme chaired by state minister for youth and sports Ahad Ali Sarkar among others was addressed by secretary to youth and sports ministry Mahbub Ahmed, director general of Directorate of Youth Development Fakhrul Islam. bd
